## Example 3 — Solve an Exponential Equation by Using Logarithms

Solve:

`11^x = 101`

Round to the nearest ten-thousandth.

Take the common logarithm of both sides:

`log 11^x = log 101`

Use the Power Property:

`x log 11 = log 101`

Solve for `x`:

`x = log 101 / log 11`

`x ≈ 1.9247`

### Check

The solution can also be checked graphically by comparing `y = 11^x` and `y = 101`.

